cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.RO 

This paper is about attacking agents trained by deep reinforcement learning algorithms using adversarial examples. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since these fields are closely related to deep reinforcement learning. The paper also discusses the potential security risks of deep reinforcement learning, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper applies the tactics to Atari games, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
